  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing Essential Services to Respond to the COVID-19 Pandemic in Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through the proposed project and envisioned activities, IOM is aiming to contribute to the containment of the spread of the COVID-19 pandemic and minimize mortality and morbidity rates in Sudan through the implementation of: (1) infection prevention control (IPC) measures, (2) essential water, sanitation and hygiene (WASH) services for health facilities, isolation and points of entry/exit (PoEs), and camps and camp-like settings; (3) risk communication community engagement (RCCE) activities; (4) income generating activities to mitigate the negative socio-economic impact of COVID-19; and (5) COVID-19 IDPs camp coordination activities.</narrative>
  </description>
